1.1 Objectives  
Digitisation, AI and BD technologies are currently being developed, tried and deployed differently, at different maturity levels between the different process industries and organisational functions. This represents both a challenge and an opportunity for us in the European process industry. A challenge because the benefits of AI and BD solutions to optimise the process towards the SPIRE vision of sustainable and competitive process industries are not equally being realised in all the process industry sectors or processes. At the same time, this also offers us an opportunity, as positive experiences with AI and BD in one process industry sector can be adapted and transferred to another, once it has become clear what their benefits are and how further development towards AI and big data business cases can be pursued.  

Our AI-CUBE project aims to tackle this challenge and leverage this opportunity by identifying the use and penetration of AI and BD in each of the process industries and organisational processes, as a basis for cross-sectorial knowledge and technology transfer and to design business case-oriented roadmaps for the European process industries of the future.  

The overall objective of our AI-CUBE project is to contribute to harnessing and optimising the potential of AI and BD in the European process industry by defining a roadmap that serves as guidance for us as researchers, managers, and operators, with specific recommendations for all involved industrial sectors and organisations’ functions and processes. To achieve this, our specific objectives of AI-CUBE are:  

1. draw a 4-dimensional AI and BD map (or a “CUBE”) where good practices are available within the different organisational processes across the eight SPIRE process industries, assessing the current state-of-play and level of penetration of AI and BD within the different organisational processes across the 8 SPIRE process industry sectors;  
2. identify good practices to build on towards future AI and BD business cases and define the RD&I actions needed in a roadmap per sector;  
3. detect the white spots of AI and BD solutions that can be covered by good practices from other process industries, and outline the roadmap towards adapting good practices for other sectors;
